CHANGES
====================
This file provides the revision history of TLA+ Toolbox project. It contain Revision information stated one after 
the other with latest on the top, each of which has the following format:   

{yyyy-mm-dd} "{logical-version-tag}" ["{Revision description}"]
-------------------------------
DESCRIPTION: {General description of the release
 which is usually a short multi-line text.}
- {CATEGORY}: "{Description of the change}" 
- {CATEGORY}: "{Description of the change}"
...

{CATEGORY} is one of the BUGFIX, CHANGE, FEATURE 

2009-xx-xx "0.0.2" 
---------------------------------------------------
- TODO(LL): help content
- TODO(SZ): module actions to react on the module (PCal translation to enable only on PCal modules)

- FEATURE: Support of model locking (TLC runs on a copy, the original is read only.)
- FEATURE: Editor improvements: folding of multi-line comments, syntax highlighting, content assist, hyper-linking (ctrl + click), goto definition (F3)    
- BUGFIX : Links on the 1st page of ModelEditor 
- BUGFIX : Problem with parse status indicator not disappearing in welcome perspective
- BUGFIX : fast views forgets about the views that are opened on restart 
- FEATURE: Specification Explorer (new, open, delete, rename, properties)
- FEATURE: Model Explorer (new, open, rename, delete, clone)
- FEATURE: TLC run as external process (interruptible)
- FEATURE: icons
- FEATURE: splash branding
- FEATURE: Model creation dialog added
- FEATURE: TLC Launch creates the _MC module to launch on
- FEATURE: TLC configuration added (called model)
- FEATURE: TLC launch added
- FEATURE: PCal runs as a job
- FEATURE: Pcal translates module using the module preferences for PCal run
- CHANGE : Menu redesign
- FEATURE: Console added
- FEATURE: introduction page added
- FEATURE: simple error report of Pcal errors
- FEATURE: Pcal translation starts with CTRL + T
- BUGFIX : The bug in the check that the root file is a TLA file. 
- FEATURE: PCal translation added
- FEATURE: Preferences on auto-build added (module, spec, files)
- BUGFIX : On switched off auto-build and shown "Problems View", the view is not repainted on save of a modified file 
- FEATURE: In the editors tabs, root modules are marked with a special symbol
- FEATURE: In the list of modules in "Open Module" sub-menu marks the root module with specific icon
- FEATURE: The Parse Specification (root module) can be triggered by CTRL + R shortcut
- CHANGE : Problem View toggling is looking on the problems, not on the spec status (this avoid empty problem view window to be shown ever) 
- BUGFIX : If the Problem View is shown and the build happens it reopens with the new errors (if any errors)
- FEATURE: Help button now only opens the content help
- FEATURE: Context help activated (hitting F1 everywhere)  
- FEATURE: On errors reported from SANY located in modules, which are not yet part of the Spec-Project (linked-in) the resources 
will become part of the project
- FEATURE: "Open module" menu, based on SANY run
- FEATURE: "Open module" menu displays the module names sorted alphabetically ignoring case
- FEATURE: Sorts the error messages in the "Problem View" by severity desc, resource name desc, line number asc.
- FEATURE: Add module to the spec with OS-based dialog
- FEATURE: "Create new spec" allows to pick an non-existent root file, which will be created.
- FEATURE: On changes in a file the dependency list is considered before rebuild 
- CHANGE : Status "semantic warning" has been added to the resolution of the parse status. It is marked by the warning 
written on the yellow background. The warning is a problem status and causes the problem window to pop-up.
- CHANGE : The defaults for preferences "spacesForTabs" and "lineNumberRuler" has been changed
- BUGFIX : The parse status "Could not find module" is handled correctly. The Marker is attached to the Spec itself. 
- BUGFIX : The parse status widget is shown from the beginning on and is permanently visible
- BUGFIX : System.err redirected prior starting of the SANY

2009-01-28 "0.0.1" 
---------------------------------------------------
